This paper proposes a modification to existing neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new component, the contextual parameter generator (CPG), which generates the parameters of the system, making it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two datasets, which involves processing text and potentially using image data, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
